sm::eod::EngineStateOutputData

EngineStateOutputData Class Reference

#include <enginestateoutputdata.h>

Inherits EngineOutputBase.

List of all members.

Detailed Description

Contains status information common to all types of Seeing Machines tracking engines.

Different types of tracking engines are able to attach different sub-objects representing detailed internal state information from each processor in the pipeline.

Member Enumeration Documentation

anonymous enum

Possible engine states.

Enumerator:
INVALID  The engine is not created or has been destroyed or an internal error has occured.
IDLE  The engine is not running (minimumal CPU state). It is idling (consuming video) however all image processing is disabled (no tracking).
RUNNING  The engine is running. Image-processing / tracking is occuring.
